President Obama has declared a major disaster in California due to the tsunami waves that struck the state on March 11, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Del Norte and Santa Cruz Counties. The funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, federal funding will be provided for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Sandy Coachman has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.